subject: p16853729
Findings: There is chronic blunting of the left lateral costophrenic angle potentially due to atelectasis or small effusion. There may be mild vascular congestion but without overt edema. Linear left basilar opacity is likely atelectasis. Cardiomediastinal silhouette is stable. No acute osseous abnormalities. PEG tube projects over the abdomen.
